Dispatch within 1 Day from Sydney with Australia Post. All the watches are shipped with local and an international manufacturers warranty, an instruction manual and original packaging

Seiko automatic with manual wind men's watch SRPD29K1. The mechanical movement 4R36 of the SRPD29 with a number of 24 jewels has the functions: hour, minute, second, date, weekday. Made of stainless steel, this is waterproof tested to 20 bar / 200 m. The silver dial is protected by a scratch resistant hardlex glass. The diameter of the SRPD29 measured without the crown is about 44 mm. The housing height is 13 mm. The Gangrereserve in this automatic clock is fully charged> 41h.

Features:

Automatic movement Caliber: 4R36 analog 24 jewels

Watch glass: scratch-resistant, hardened mineral glass / hard glass with date magnifier

Elevator mechanism: Double-sided automatic winding (magic lever)

Water resist: 20 bar

Dial: black dial with applied, highly polished stainless steel indexes. The indices are filled in with luminescent Lumibrite luminescent mass

Hands: Stainless steel hour hand, minute hand and second hand. All hands are also coated with Lumibrite luminescent material for easy readability in the dark

Belt clasp: Safety folding clasp with safety handles and safety bar with engraved Seiko lettering

Magnetic resistance: 4800 A / m (amperes per meter)

Band: black ion-plated stainless steel bracelet with additional diver extension

Bracelet width: The bracelet width of the stainless steel band is 20,0 - 27,2 mm (measured at the band stop)

Display: hour, minute, second, date and weekday (weekday display in German / English)

Housing: Stainless steel housing with dark gray titanium carbide support and screwed stainless steel bottom

Special feature: one-sided rotatable, precisely locking bezel

Power reserve: greater 41 hours power reserve

Bracelet length: The bracelet length is about 215 mm

Case diameter (without crown) 42 mm

Case height: 13 mm

Weight: The Seiko Monster SRPD29 weighs 187 grams
